    <!-- Accessibility Disclosure (Play Store compliance) -->
    <string name="accessibility_disclosure_title">How Focus Shield Uses Accessibility</string>
    <string name="accessibility_disclosure_body">Focus Shield uses the Android Accessibility Service exclusively to:\n\n• Detect when short-form content surfaces (Reels, Shorts, Stories, Explore feeds) are displayed\n• Read URL bars in browsers to block configured websites\n• Identify which screen within a monitored app is active\n\nFocus Shield does NOT:\n• Read your private messages, passwords, or personal data\n• Collect or transmit any content you view\n• Modify or interact with other apps on your behalf\n• Record your screen or take screenshots\n\nAll detection happens entirely on your device. No data leaves your phone unless you explicitly enable cloud sync features.\n\nYou can disable this permission at any time in Settings → Accessibility.</string>

